  "_doc": "Daemon protocol drift gate fixtures. Each entry pins one UDS op's wire contract: the request shape the daemon accepts and the response shape it emits. Consumed by two gates: (1) Rust integration test asserts handler output contains every `response_required_keys` entry; (2) Go test in clients/go/leyline-schema/daemon/ asserts the response JSON decodes into the matching typed binding without UnmarshalTypeError. Together they pin handler→schema agreement. Extends T8.10's cross-runtime fixture pattern (bead 6b7d43) from segment-file substrate to the JSON wire. Post-b0ea2e: the wire is generated by capnp-json (C++ JsonCodec compatible) — Int64/UInt64 emit as JSON strings, capnp Int defaults emit as `\"0\"` (no skip-if-default annotation), and `enrichment_typed` is a typed List(EnrichmentEntry) (the legacy `enrichment` Text field is deliberately not emitted by the daemon — kept in the schema per ADR-0014 §2 but unset on the wire, so the field is absent from the JSON). See docs/TABLE_CONTRACT.md.",

